
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `avinfo` baraye gereftan etela'at darbareye file-haye multimedia, mesle film-ha va ahang-ha, estefade mishavad. In dastoor format, codec, bitrate, va etela'ate digar ra namayesh midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `avinfo filename.mp4`  --> 🎬 Namayesh etela'at asasi file
    🔹 `avinfo -v frames filename.mp4`  --> 🎞️ Namayesh etela'at har frame az video
    🔹 `avinfo -i filename.mp3`  --> 🎵 Namayesh etela'at file audio
    🔹 `avinfo -f format_name filename` --> 🗂️ Estefade az yek format khas baraye tahlil

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ avinfo video.mp4

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at kamel darbareye file video.mp4

    $ avinfo audio.mp3

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at kamel darbareye file audio.mp3

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ avinfo mymovie.avi | grep Duration

    🔹 Peyda kardan va namayesh dadane modat zaman (Duration) az file `mymovie.avi`.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `avinfo` command is used to retrieve information about multimedia files, such as movies and songs. This command displays the format, codec, bitrate, and other details.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `avinfo filename.mp4`  --> 🎬 Show basic file information
    🔹 `avinfo -v frames filename.mp4`  --> 🎞️ Show information for each video frame
    🔹 `avinfo -i filename.mp3`  --> 🎵 Show audio file information
    🔹 `avinfo -f format_name filename` --> 🗂️ Use a specific format for analysis

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ avinfo video.mp4

    🔹 Display complete information about the video.mp4 file.

    $ avinfo audio.mp3

    🔹 Display complete information about the audio.mp3 file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ avinfo mymovie.avi | grep Duration

    🔹 Find and display the duration from the file `mymovie.avi`.

